          <div class="blog-detail-text-box">
            <p>
              Securing your Intellectual Property involves several key
              instruments. Trademarks protect your brand identity—your name and
              logo—preventing others from using a similar mark that could
              confuse consumers. Patents grant you exclusive rights to your
              inventions, allowing you to control their commercial use.
              Copyright safeguards your original creative and literary works,
              from software code to website content. At O. A. Omonuwa SAN & Co.,
              we provide comprehensive counsel on identifying, registering, and
              defending your intellectual property rights, ensuring that your
              most valuable assets are secure as you grow.
            </p>
